report_cell_edge_type(25.10)                      report_cell_edge_type(25.10)

Name
       report_cell_edge_type - Reports the edge type of the specified cell

Syntax
       report_cell_edge_type

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       [-file <fileName>]

       Reports the edge type of the specified cell.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the cell name for which edge type is to be reported.

              If  the  cell name is not specified, all the cell edge types are
              reported in the edge_type.rpt file report file.

       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the report file name.

              If no file name is specified, the edge_type.rpt file is used  to
              generate the report.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each report_cell_edge_type parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man report_cell_edge_type.

Related Information
              * specifyCellEdgeType

              * deleteCellEdgeType

